Sentencas: La2NiO4+-based oxides, mixed ionic-electronic conductors with K2NiF4-type structure, have been considerably investigated in recent decades as electrode materials for advanced solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) due to their high electrical conductivity and oxidation reduction reaction (ORR) activity.
Titulo: La1.7Ca0.3Ni0.75Cu0.25O4--Layered Perovskite as Cathode on La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3 or Ce0.8Gd0.2O2 Electrolyte for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: In this study, La1.7Ca0.3Ni0.75Cu0.25O4+ was investigated as a potential cathode on La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3 electrolyte support.
Titulo: La1.7Ca0.3Ni0.75Cu0.25O4--Layered Perovskite as Cathode on La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3 or Ce0.8Gd0.2O2 Electrolyte for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Furthermore, La1.7Ca0.3Ni0.75Cu0.25O4+ was examined on thin Ce0.8Gd0.2O2 (GDC) electrolyte with Ni-GDC anode support for intermediate temperature SOFCs (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: La1.7Ca0.3Ni0.75Cu0.25O4--Layered Perovskite as Cathode on La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3 or Ce0.8Gd0.2O2 Electrolyte for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
